Kocherlakota Says Markets Have Lots of ‘Faith’ in Treasuries

-- B y   V i v i e n   L o u   C h e n   a n d   N a d j a   B r a n d t
-- 
2011-05-05T18:05:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/kocherlakota-says-markets-have-lots-of-faith-in-treasuries.html
Federal Reserve Bank of Minneapolis
President Narayana Kocherlakota said markets have a lot of
“faith” in U.S. Treasuries and the “best thing” policy
makers can do for the dollar is to fulfill the Fed’s mandate to
ensure stable prices and maximum employment.  Kocherlakota spoke in response to audience questions after
a speech in  Santa Barbara ,  California .  To contact the reporters on this story:
Vivien Lou Chen in  San Francisco  at 
 vchen1@bloomberg.net ;
Nadja Brandt in Santa Barbara, California, at 
 nbrandt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz in Washington at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net  